< text>
This gym exceeded expectations. As a downtown local I was looking for a new gym and stumbled upon Fit. The facility had all the equipment I was looking for, friendly staff, super clean and was huge! They even had outdoor decks to workout on and a heated pool and jacuzzi. Not to mention prime view of Petco Park in time for this season. I highly recommend checking this place out, you won't be disappointed!</text>

< Review>
I am very disappointed with Fit Mission Beach Customer Service since the first time I've been there.
I was wearing shorts and flip-flops - ready to go to the beach on a Saturday morning.

When I arrived there, the sales rep started to show me the membership prices and discussing it right away. I asked "you're not going to show me the gym first?" Then he said "I just want to make sure you're aware of our pricing". What does it mean? Did I look like I didn't have financial conditions to pay for the membership?
Then I asked him about a discount of course. I am a business woman. I work with purchasing for years and also have sales and customer service experience. Of course I'll try to negotiate everything. Then he said there was no discount available, and in sum, that they don't need to offer any discount since they have enough customers already.

I was impressed with the location, but very disappointed with this very poor customer service. Even though, I really wanted to work out with that view. So I went to downtown location just to sign up with a different person. I had a very nice experience with Rachel, so I closed the deal.
Today, 3 weeks later, I had a very bad experience with the manager AARON BAZZ.

The gym was closing. I was so focused and exhausted that I didn't realize by the time. So this manager came to me to say the gym was closed that I had to leave. I was like "ok, I didn't realized the time". So I left the training room and went outside to sit for 1 minute. This manager came to me again saying "I told you the gym is closed and you have to leave". I said "I am just breathing. Can I just stay to breath for 1 minute?" He said "No!! You have to leave right now!!"

I didn't even waste my time arguing. He treated me with total disrespect, was not kind, polite at all! He was super rude and I will not tolerate this kind of treatment from no one.
That's an expensive gym compared to the others, and the "cheaper" ones never treated me like that, with such disrespect and very bad customer service.

The gym looks nice, the location is nice, but totally not worth it for this very bad customer service. I live in San Diego for over 5 years and never been treated like that!< /Review>

This is a late entry to my short experience here before covid happened. Great facility and equipments but the customer service is so unpleasant. <response>None<//response><pictures>None</pictures>< review>
I've been going to Fit for the better part of a year now and it is by far the best gym I have ever belonged to. The moment you walk inside you can tell that this won't be like your typical gym experience. From the towel service they provide, the the spa-like conditions of the locker room, to the view directly into Petco Park...it really doesn't get any better.

The staff have always been friendly and helpful to me. The machines have always been in awesome condition and working properly give or take the inevitable breakdown that is usually fixed quickly. I go at what I would consider the beginning of peak hours for a gym and I rarely have to wait for equipment. Honestly, one of my favorite things about the gym is the clientele. When you are paying a premium for your gym, you better believe you are taking your fitness seriously. I love being surrounded by like-minded individuals that clearly have a passion for fitness, but aren't there to judge the people around them.

The price might be higher than most gyms in the area, but you get what you pay for. I personally could not be happier.</review>

< Text>
The equipment is dated, the organization is bad, the flooring throughout is designed for small lifting platforms, not a gym floor because it's not designed for walking, just impact lifting. The floor is the wild west, with a number of people that simply don't know gym etiquette, or fundamental lifting, and did I mention the equipment is 'dated'. There is no speciality of the gym, yoga, functional classes, fusion training room, cardio and stretching, it's all like a bad buffet where there's a lot of it, but nothing good. The lockers couldn't make code if they opened today, and maintenance is non existent.

Customer service? Good luck w finding that too...if u want consistent parking, you'll need to buy that from ACE parking downtown... $100 month, again, if they opened today, their parking would not be sufficient to get a permit to operate...

All this, and a cool 80-100 month to go...if u must try it, do it for 30 days, no matter 'what' cool program they're offering 'that day only'... trust me, if you like this type of training, go to 24 hour fitness downtown at Horton... $25 month, $25 annual to renew, plenty of parking. And even though it's not great, it's better than this FIT facility, at a fraction of the cost, which is what it'd be worth.</Text>

< review>
I like the club downtown ! I like the staff! I like the fact all machines are clean and get repaired very fast.
The members are respectful and well mannered .
The parking situation can be difficult as u may be stuck sometimes for 10 or 15 minutes when someone is not able to pay on way out.
Putting ur membership on hold is an ordeal .
Every year I take few months off .
Last year they kept charging me as I notified the administration I was leaving for few months .
I decided to let go and forget a refund.
This year they did the same thing! They charged me 2 months as they were properly notified !
First they could not find my email notifying them I was leaving for few
Minth.
They then decided to refund one month. Then after resenting all documentation then they accepted to refund me 2 months . I am not sure if they are disorganized or what! But I wasted a lot of time to get
Back my money!< /review>

<user_id>100766571463885099805</user_id><username>Matthew Bruhin<//username><Time>1539798399992< /Time><rating>1</rating><Review>It is so sad to have to write this review. I have complaiend about this young woman more than once to management, about the absolute horrific treatment and customer service of this front desk attendant. She never smiles, is curt, rude and lacks any basic customer service skills.

This past weekend I had my wallet stolen including all my credit cards. Despite my explanation to the young woman at the front desk - and fact that I am in here almost daily - this attendant refused me admittance until I had a new card on file. I had to literally return to my car in the basement and retrieve my temporary wallet and another temp. atm card, and then had to deal with her nasty demeanor as I asked why she was rude and forced me to leave the gym and provide a card I did not want have yet. I am certain she is aware of my complaints about her attitude in the past but felt on this weekend, whithout managment on site, she could exact her revenge.

In addition to Fit, I hold memberships at Chuze fitness and YMCA. While their gyms are not as nice or flashy, they are the most friendly, smiling and courteous staff in the business. While Fit is visibly nice, it is extremely expensive. The attitude and lack of customer service adds up and this was the final straw. As a CEO, I know how crucial friendly customer service is in any business. This continued staffing of people who are rude, wil not earn or retain my business. I hope this message rings true and that changes are made, as the gym itself is a wonderful venue for fitness.

He stated he would ‚Äútalk‚Äù with her, offered no recourse or way to make up for the event. Jessie Womble< /name>
<Time>1375042973840< /Time><Rating>5<//Rating>< review>
have been a member of FIT for almost 2 years and am so pleased with my experience there.   I have never been one for fancy gyms that intimidate you with all of the intense people walking around and taking up classes.  So I was a bit apprehensive when I joined but decided to give it a try.   I had tried everything from 24-hour fitness, to Frogs, to La Jolla Sporting Club, to the YMCA,  and more.  All delivered either a subpar customer service experience (where I felt like just a number), were too "posh" that I felt self conscious, classes were always full or instructors were routinely late.

I have been pleased to find that FIT is the best of all worlds - beautiful, clean, modern gym with all the amenities you could ask for PLUS amazing classes, fantastic/motivating instructions (no matter your fitness level), a small cafe/food area with fresh ideas on nutrition, and the list goes on!

I have finally found my gym for life!  Thank you FIT!</review>

< text>
Pros: Great equipment variety
Lot of room to workout
Rarely gets crowded
You get towel service
Tons of ameneties; pool, sauna, steam room, heated yoga, crossfit

Cons: The Hours are horrible, they close at 10pm and weekends open at 7am
When something breaks it will stay broken for at least a month
The AC does not work during summer or maybe they just dont want to turn it on but it feels really stuffy

Do good research before you commit yourself to something it might be worth it for some might not be for others,

PS also be sure to google some of the other people who have commented/rated here notice they are mostly employees/ affiliates so dont go by all the ratings / comments DO YOUR RESEARCH</text>

<user>114322485185096172282< /user>< user_name>
cheryl cash< /user_name>
< Time>
1270427062687</Time>
< rate>
1<//rate>
< Review>
I belong to this gym.  I like that it is downtown and that the facilities accomadate a large flow.  The classes however are all close together for after work hours and the classes are jammed. Though there are several styles of fitness classes, most of them all feel like the same thing different name or instructor.

This gym charges a lot for additional classes and I believe it has over valued itself as a luxury fitness center.  Platnum membership is about 500.00 per month and I just do not feel the gym meets its price.  Regular membership is 100.00 plus per month.

The sales guys all seem to hang out at the top of the railing on the second floor giving an uneasy feeling to newcomers.  It feels a lot like the "IN" club, both with sales and staff.  Not so sure I am as impressed with the gym and it's atmosphere as when I signed up.

Good things:  Great locker rooms always kept clean.  Though the seats are showing rips in the seams already. Lockers are coded, so no need for bringing a lock.  Towels are good and kept stocked for both the shower and the fitness room.

Steam room and Saunas in both mens and womens locker rooms.  I like the privacy of this.

Unbearable things:  MUSIC Ultra LOUD.  Pool not a lap pool.  Jacuzzi is broke most of the time.  No lotions or cotton balls or mouth wash supplied in locker rooms.(look at the price and you will agree that these things should be provided including razors for shaving.)  Equipment is often not kept up with, lots of machines broken for months.

I have belonged to private resort set style gyms in the past and all amenities were included in pricing.

A bit of a big let down.  Was not impressed with my personal training either.  Just has a glossy look and some of the sparkle of extras but not fully making the cut.  Will not renew my membership<//Review>

<Text>First off let me say that if you‚Äôre going to want to open your restaurant in United States of America then you need to learn the laws of the land and that includes that service dogs are allowed into every store and restaurant in the public arena. When I walked in the owner lady kept trying to tell me I needed to sit outside and I kept telling her service dogs are allowed inside and I finally said look the federal government allows service dogs to accompany their owner because of a medical reason if you don‚Äôt understand that then you should not be owning a business here.  So she finally let me inside with my service dog. I was told that these people have had a business for 10 years and that‚Äôs more than enough time that they should know things like this.

Also usually with Indian food there are at least a couple dishes that are mild and not spicy. Such as the samosas or the lentil soup‚Äòs or the tiki masala‚Äòs. My husband ordered a couple of these items because other other Indian restaurants they are mild enough that there is no heat and only flavor to the seasoning. The lentil soup is not mildly spice as it says in a samosas had quite a bit of what I‚Äôm guessing is cardamom and made it way too spicy for him to be able to eat it so we basically wasted some of our money.

The owner also took forever to get our food out as well as over 10 minutes to bring us our ticket when we asked to pay when there was only one other group in the restaurant. <Review>I cannot say enough great things about the maintenance staff here! Since moving in October of last year (from out of state), they have been pleasant and courteous with every request. I have two dogs (one is a new and very vocal rescue), so I have begun noting that I need to be home for my work orders.

During this time of COVID, they called to schedule an appointment to fix a sticking gas burner. On the day of the appointment, they knocked, but I asked that they reschedule as I needed to take one of the dogs to an emergency vet appointment. Both guys were very understanding and told me that they could be back later on in the day, to which I agreed. Unfortunately, the vet appointment took longer than anticipated, so I missed the time a second time!

I resubmitted the work order a week later with a note for a Tuesday or Wednesday date. On Monday afternoon, the maintenance techs gave me a call to set a time on Tuesday afternoon. They arrived promptly, and quickly fixed the issue, and then had me test it to make sure that everything was working well. While they were in the apartment, I asked about a few minor things (replacing blinds and the air filter), and they offered to get the replacements for me right then and there.

Anthony (who is the newest maintenance technician) made me feel at ease with his amazing customer service. Instead of silently doing the task in the kitchen while I was in the living room, he introduced himself and was very friendly while being trained by Frank.

Frank was quick and efficient, and did everything with a smile. He explained everything to me that he was doing as he did it, and was the one to offer to check the vents after I asked. He has great insight and was so polite with my thousands of questions.

If you have any concerns about any small issues in the apartments here (it happens everywhere), then you should feel comfortable knowing these guys have got you covered!< /Review><pictures>None<//pictures>< resp>

< text>
The Villas At Towngate is my home and I'm happy I chose here for my first apartment. I love the layout of my apartment and I always get compliments on the pool area and kind staff.
My only complaints are NO pets, so I had to leave my cat at home with my mother; parking can be difficult, and parking can be hard to find sometimes. Keep in mind you get 3 passes for guests. Make sure they place them on their cars or they will be towed. There is also parking on the street and you could park at Winco and walk over to the Villas.
For a single woman stepping out on her own I have to say THANK YOU to the maintenance crew. They are always on top of it to help me. My air condition was acting up and they came early the next day to fix it. On another occasion a guest messed with my alarm system and it went off like crazy and wouldn't turn off. Maintenance and security came to make sure everything was okay and handled the minor emergency quickly. Maintenance are always polite and you can request they call before entering or allow them to enter while you're away. Security walks about sometimes but anytime I called they came quickly to either quiet a loud nuisance, etc. And the front desk is always helpful during their hours to handle minor concerns like neighbor disputes. This is a friendly location for all kinds of people from families to single occupants.
I might pay a bit more than the rest of the MoVal area for my one bedroom but I'm guaranteed safe. I left my door open accidentally one night and nothing bad happened. I've also never seen a vehicle broken into like other apartment complexes.<//text>

< text>
In January of this year, I hired Twin on behalf of the homebuyer I was representing to inspect the home she was in process of purchasing. The home was vacant at the time of inspection and Twin was hired to do a full home inspection. Not long after the completion of the purchase, we discovered what appeared to be mold growing on the ceiling of the living room. When we discovered this, we sent a contractor into the attic to check the area. The contractor was able to access the affected area of the attic without issue, in less than five minutes. He was able to clearly see that the plywood roof sheathing directly above the area of the moldy ceiling was wet and moldy as well. It seemed that this should have been noted by the home inspector as the attic was easily accessible and empty at the time of inspection. So, I contacted the home inspector and he said I would hear from his manager. Well, that didn‚Äôt happen. So I followed-up and finally received an email from the manager basically stating that Twin isn‚Äôt responsible as the issue was in the attic and the full attic was not inspected. I respond to this email with‚Ä¶Huh? You say that the accessible areas of the attic were inspected in your report. How was this area inaccessible to you? The contractor that discovered the issue had no problem getting to it‚Ä¶ And I get no response whatsoever. In the meantime, the homebuyer has sent several emails as well, with no response. She even sent a certified letter with NO RESPONSE. You get the idea. Well, we finally get a response just a couple days AFTER the homebuyer writes a review on YELP! I guess that got their attention. So in JULY, they finally agree verbally to refund the cost of the home inspection to my homebuyer. But wait, then they tell me that they won‚Äôt give my homebuyer a refund unless she removes the YELP review! Here‚Äôs what the email said‚Ä¶ ‚ÄúThe reasons that we would be willing to refund the inspection fee are: 1) I'm not happy with our initial communication and response to your issue. 2) We have a win-win resolution. Your clients get money towards their expenses and we can turn an angry situation into a good one. IN THE PROCESS WE DO NOT SUFFER A POOR REVIEW. At no point during our discussions back and forth did anyone from Twin say that the homebuyers refund was contingent upon her removing her review from Yelp. Twin is clearly using refunds as a means to control their online reviews which shows just how unprofessional they truly are.< /text>

<Review>Hello there!

On day three of our trip to California, we decided to head to Huntington Beach for the day. We really enjoy Huntington Beach and it was only a 30 minute drive from our hotel in Anaheim.  The beach is great and the local shops are fun to browse and the even the neighborhoods are nice to take a stroll through.

Of course, we wanted to eat, something my husband and I do well, and often, especially on trips.

As we walked Main Street to make our decision of where we would eat, we decided on Sugar Shack Cafe at 213 Main Street, Huntington Beach, CA.

Since it was breakfast, not that it matters, my husband opted for the Spanish Omelet and I had the Kepper's Benedict.

We both agreed that the Keeper's was better than the Spanish Omelet. The sauce that was on the omelet was not that great. It tasted and looked like a watery tomato juice. Even the flavor of the omelet was not that great.

We sat outside and enjoyed watching people pass by as we ate.

The service was there, the hostess and waitress were nice and the atmosphere was great. Being from Tucson, we are not fans of sitting outside to eat - the heat is a little much but in Huntington Bach sitting outside was enjoyable with the breeze and the temperature.

All in all it was good. Just a little disappointing in the omelet. Little flavor and some watery sauce.< /Review><userid>101860354992201750199</userid>< GmapID>
0x80dd214162ec8ced:0x7ffe8c595904074f< /GmapID>

< text>
Altho a "regular" breakfast spot near the beach on Main St with eggs and the basics, Sugar Shack is far from regular with basics.

From some of the far better menu items to almost everyone working there being far from average, this place gets my 6 star rating!

When I say far from average people, from some of the best surfers in HB & beyond to people who care, going beyond the typical call of server duty to ensure your time there is pleasant, your food is served quickly, comfortably and your coffee is full!< /text>

</record></dataset><record>
<GmapID>0x80dd214162ec8ced:0x7ffe8c595904074f< /GmapID><pictures>None<//pictures>< date>
1610487985447<//date>
<rating>5< /rating><response>None</response><user>110753367084927927004< /user><username>Bob Thompson</username>< Review>
Sugar Shack Cafe is a great place to have breakfast in Huntington Beach.  The servers are friendly, the food always comes out quick and hot, and they don't skimp on the food they serve you.

There are three dining areas on the premises.  The first and most notable is their front patio.  This is a great place to people watch.  You may have to sign in and wait, to sit in this area, as it's the most popular.  Inside is always cramped, but they have some great old surfing photos of Huntington Beach on the walls to gander at.  There is a fairly large patio in the back, where you usually won't have to wait to be seated.

My favorite here is a ham, mushroom & Swiss cheese omelette.  This beauty comes out oozing with cheese, packed with smoky ham steak chunks and sliced sauteed mushrooms.  Very buttery tasting, as well.  YUM.  Hash browns are perfectly golden brown & crispy.

My wife and I would come here early on the weekend, whenever we were headed to Bolsa Chica Ecological Reserve, to do some birding.  If you can get here around 8am on weekends, then you'll beat the rush.  Parking can be difficult to find on Main St., but they do have several parking garages close by on Main St., just north of the Sugar Shack, one on each side of the street.

They are also famous for their French toast here.  So yummy!</Review>
</record>

101860354992201750199</user_id>
<Name>Randal and Jesus Higby-Giron< /Name><date>1569168223955<//date><rate>3<//rate>< text>
Hello there!

On day three of our trip to California, we decided to head to Huntington Beach for the day. We really enjoy Huntington Beach and it was only a 30 minute drive from our hotel in Anaheim.  The beach is great and the local shops are fun to browse and the even the neighborhoods are nice to take a stroll through.

Of course, we wanted to eat, something my husband and I do well, and often, especially on trips.

As we walked Main Street to make our decision of where we would eat, we decided on Sugar Shack Cafe at 213 Main Street, Huntington Beach, CA.

Since it was breakfast, not that it matters, my husband opted for the Spanish Omelet and I had the Kepper's Benedict.

We both agreed that the Keeper's was better than the Spanish Omelet. The sauce that was on the omelet was not that great. It tasted and looked like a watery tomato juice. Even the flavor of the omelet was not that great.

We sat outside and enjoyed watching people pass by as we ate.

The service was there, the hostess and waitress were nice and the atmosphere was great. Being from Tucson, we are not fans of sitting outside to eat - the heat is a little much but in Huntington Bach sitting outside was enjoyable with the breeze and the temperature.

All in all it was good. Just a little disappointing in the omelet. Little flavor and some watery sauce.< /text>

<pictures>None< /pictures><text>URGENT/ BE AWARE!
My husband and I were in the Sugar Shack yesterday 9.13.19 for an enjoyable breakfast, when our order came it was very concerning. There was obvious mold on the two slices of bread, the eggs were under cooked and it continues from there. As my husband was eating he realized the food seemed very off and he first sent the toast back, the waiter noticed the mold and was nice about accepting it back. Another server brought back more toast however, it was evident it came from the same loaf just at the tail end.
My dish did not taste fresh and I left all of it behind. My husband had eaten one of the two eggs and left his meal aside. We payed our bill and left very disappointed as we have been residents in HB for 3 decades.
Shortly after, my husband became violently ill, unable to function. He was taken to the ER after a half day of torture and the doctor confirmed it was a food borne illness. I called the restaurant today hoping to notify the owner and I was told he is never around.
I am urgently writing this message because I do not want any person or child to go through what my husband just experienced. Food poisoning can be extremely dangerous.
If you are the owner reading this please FIX IT,  you are putting our community in danger. Thank you! MM</text></record>

<text>Sugar Shack is the true staple of breakfast places in downtown Huntington Beach. You get tasty food for a decent value, huge portions, and you're by the sea.

Their food is pretty much diner food. Nothing fancy but it satisfies hungry people happily. Their hash-browns cannot be beat. Their "surf" (half hot chocolate half coffee drink) is my guilty pleasure.

Whether you want a simple two egg breakfast with toast or something for a bigger appetite they have it all. I've had every kind of breakfast imaginable there and have not been disappointed.

They have outdoor seating both front (on Main St.) and back (in alleyway), as well as indoor seating. The indoor seating is first come first serve even on busy days.<//text><gmap_id>0x80dd214162ec8ced:0x7ffe8c595904074f</gmap_id><Pictures>None</Pictures><username>Deanna Fountain</username><rate>4<//rate></record>

<rate>5< /rate><Review>This is a great place. It's been around since 1967. They only serve breakfast and lunch but somehow have managed to stay in business when so many others have gone out or business. It's a local spot that has the support of the community. The food is really good and I've tasted most things on the menu over the years. It's always packed so get here early. It's worth the wait. They have a back seating area that usually is less packed than the front that has a view of main Street.</Review>< Pics>

<user>108725575210621701825</user><date>1472875380949</date>< Review>
Atmosphere was casual, awesome outdoor seating in the midst of the hustle and bustle of main street - perfect for socializing/people watching. The service was fast and friendly.

We went for lunch and couldn't resist trying "The Charger" - a yummy combination of grilled chicken breast, avocado slices, bacon, lettuce, tomato, cheddar and Monterrey cheeses, accompanied by hearty sides of buffalo and ranch sauces with crispy, thick,crinkle-cut fries on the side.

The sandwich was good but with the combination of sauces it was GREAT... and they serve breakfast all day....I'll have to go back ..</Review>

<review>Popped in for an impromptu brunch date on a Monday morning. The weather was finally sunny and we had opted to sit on the patio. Note: They do offer 2 patio areas. While the main (front) patio area is the most popular choice, they also have a back area covered patio as well.

I found our table to be pretty dirty for a restaurant. There was definitely a lot of food on the floor under our table which was a little gross to me. Looking past that, we placed our food orders...

We ordered the main street burrito and the keppler's. Both items came out pretty fast after we ordered. The food was okay, but nothing great and nothing that left me thinking wow - I have to have more of this.

<date>1451504143123</date><Response>None<//Response><UserId.>100912494903724583894<//UserId.><text>My extended family has been going here for years and I can see why!

Sugar Shack offers a good selection of breakfast items with very generous portions.

Plus, there's something on the menu for everyone, from the straightforward "eggs and bacon" types to those looking for healthier and lighter breakfast options.

The food was prepared well and the wait for both seating and food was minimal, despite mornings being fairly busy here due to the joint's increasing popularity.  The service was adequate and coffee was refilled when needed.

During busier times, this place is best suited for couples and smaller groups of 6 or less.

All in all, it's not the fanciest place to eat on the strip, nor is it the next taste sensation, but Sugar Shack is definitely good at what they do and that's delivering above-average breakfasts at a fairly reasonable price (considering the area)!<//text><Rating>4<//Rating>< user_name>
Clint Stevens</user_name>

< review>
Fun little place to sit outside on the sidewalk and people watch. The back patio has it's charm but the overwhelming odor of refuse can be jolting as it occasionally wafts in the direction of patrons. The food is average tasting and there are plenty of choices. Don't try to communicate a food allergy, however. The message of needing to have NO dairy,  communited more than one time, didn't get  through and my vacation was cut short by three days as I recovered from the unfortunate effects. I won't be returning but give this place a try at least once and decide for yourself.<//review>

< Review>
Love going to the Sugar Shack! Went this past weekend and disappointed to experience they have gone cheap on something like Ketchup! May not be a big deal to some else but when you like it on scrambled eggs, omlettes, hash browns or fries it makes a difference. It was like soup and ruined the meal experience. I don't mind refillable bottles like they have on the table for the ketchup. Just don't refill them and try to pass it off as no one will notice or care. If they cut corners there where else are they cutting corners? Charge me a few cents more but don't go cheap! I work in the restaurant industry and know the difference between condiment qualities. This was the cheapest you can buy. Sorry to have to write this post!<//Review>

<user>112730121747857005104< /user><username>Mark H.< /username>< time>
1456760656555< /time>
< rate>
2<//rate>
< Review>
Love going to the Sugar Shack! Went this past weekend and disappointed to experience they have gone cheap on something like Ketchup! May not be a big deal to some else but when you like it on scrambled eggs, omlettes, hash browns or fries it makes a difference. It was like soup and ruined the meal experience. I don't mind refillable bottles like they have on the table for the ketchup. Just don't refill them and try to pass it off as no one will notice or care. If they cut corners there where else are they cutting corners? Charge me a few cents more but don't go cheap! I work in the restaurant industry and know the difference between condiment qualities. This was the cheapest you can buy. Sorry to have to write this post!< /Review>

<Time>1499190106370< /Time><Rate>5< /Rate><Text>This place is SWEET! One of the things I was most upset about when we moved from Massachusetts was losing the breakfast joint that we often frequented (ya know, right after moving away from my family! Lol). If there is any meal that my little family likes to go out for, it's definitely breakfast and it has to be bomb!

Well, you can imagine how quickly I entered the realm of morning glory when we found Sugar Shack. The food here is amazing. I love the HSS special. It's a super delicious grilled ham, scrambled egg, and cheddar cheese breakfast sandwich that I like to add a little avocado too. Sooooo good. I still haven't had a chance to try their breakfast burrito, but I totally want to.

The people that work there are laid back and efficient. There's a nice outdoor patio on Main St and another covered patio in the back. Quick service. Great food. What else could you ask for? Oh... would you also like one of the nicest beaches in America?? Well it's really close to the beach, so if you are looking for delicious morning time food before heading there, this is the place!

The Sugar Shack is where it's at!</Text>< Pics>

<gmapID>0x80dd214162ec8ced:0x7ffe8c595904074f</gmapID><response>None< /response>< text>
-Wait time was to be expected it's a popular spot.
-Staff was excellent, seating is tight, not a great place for groups larger than 4 or 5 (7 of us all together, jammed into a 4 person table on the patio). It was really sunny so definitely bring some sunscreen if you're sitting outside.
-Park further up Main Street or on a side street and walk in, parking always bad the closer to PCH you get.
-Food came out pretty fast for a busy restaurant.
Got the eggs Benedict. Everyghing tasted very fresh, ham was exceptional. English muffin wasn't overcooked. What just made it alright was the hollandaise sauce. It was just  bland to my taste buds. I really love a tangy hollandaise sauce. Everyone else seemed to really love their food so next time I go I'll try the a breakfast burrito or omelette I think.
3-stars for just okay food. If you're a big water the eggs Benedict will leave you hungry, only comes with hash browns.<//text>
